OL,3,CHow Rachel Reeves learned to love
OL,4,Cbankers
OL,6,FSecond, Reeves seems persuaded that
OL,7,Fthe lethal capacity of the City and
OL,8,Fbanks to wreck the economy - as they
OL,9,Fdid in 2007/8 through reckless lending
OL,10,Fand investing in the pursuit of mega
OL,11,Fbonuses - has been tamed by better
OL,12,Fregulation.
OL,14,FWe'll learn, possibly at our and their
OL,15,Fcost, whether this is wishful
OL,16,Fthinking. Because what New Labour
OL,17,Flearned, ultimately at the cost of
OL,18,Fkeeping it out of office for 14 years,
OL,19,Fis that too much faith in the City is
OL,20,Fthe short route to oblivion.
